# No blanket item data edits

FrameHub item data is **per-item**. Mods, arcanes, weapons, warframes, companions, stances, and similar entries each have unique stats, functions, features, passives, elements, categories, and eligibility.

## Never

- Mass find/replace or scripted bulk patches across `src/data/mods.ts`, `weapons.ts`, `warframes.ts`, arcanes, or similar item catalogs
- Changing many items’ categories, stats, tags, or stance types in one pass “to fix a class”
- Assuming items that share a type/tag should get the same fields

## Always

- Edit **one item at a time** (or a short, explicitly reviewed list the user asked for)
- Verify each change against that item’s wiki/source behavior
- Prefer adding mappings/lookups keyed by id over rewriting item rows en masse

If many items look wrong, report the pattern and fix individually (or wait for user approval of a scoped list)—do not ship a blanket transform.
